{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χάραξ</b> [χᾰ], ᾰκος, ὁ, <br /> also ἡ, (χαράσσω) <b>pointed stake</b>: especially, <br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2> <b>vine-prop, pole,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 986, “V.” 1201, “Pax” 1263, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.70, “BGU” 1122.17 (1st c.BC): proverbial ἐξηπάτησεν ἡ χ. τὴν ἄμπελον,\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] of those who trust in a 'broken reed', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1291. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>pale,</b> used in fortifying the entrenchments of a camp, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ach.” 1178, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.167 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; = Latin <i>vallus,</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.29.3, 18.18.1: \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> collectively, ={χαράκωμα}, <b>palisaded camp,</b> Theophil.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Comedy texts 9, “SIG” 363.1 (Ephesus, 3rd c.BC), 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 77, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Caesar” 17 (_plural_), 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 2.60b; τὰν ἐκτὸς τοῦ χ. χώραν “IG” 42(1).76.21 (Epid., 2nd c.BC)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>palisade,</b> χάρακα βαλέσθαι πρὸς τῇ πόλει (variant{χαράκωμα}) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.87 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; = Latin <i>vallum,</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 1.80.11, 3.45.5, +others, NT.Luke.19.43 \">NT+2nd c.BC+</a>]; χάρακα τίθεσθαι form <b>an entrenched camp,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 6.29; χ. βαλέσθαι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Aemilius Paulus” 17, compare “Marc.” 18, etc.; βάλλειν [prev. author] “Sull.” 28 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; ἀποταφρεύειν, περιταφρεύειν,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 21, “Luc.” 31; διασπᾶν [prev. author] “Ant.” 18; χ. σεσιδηρωμένος καὶ ἁλύσεσι δεδεμένος 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 19.83; χ. κύκλῳ τῆς νεώς 4th c.BC: Moschio Tragicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 5.208d. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>cutting, slip,</b> especially of an olive, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 2.1.2, “CP” 5.1. [4], “Geoponica” 9.11.5 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of other plants, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 1.12.9. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> collectively, ={ἀκανθώδη φυτά}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> a seafish, one of the <b>breams, Sargus,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Diphilus Siphnius Rerum Naturalium Scriptor cited in Ath 8.355e, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 1.173 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; also a fish of the Red Sea, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 12.25. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__V</b></Level2> name of a <b>bandage,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Heliodorus Medicus cited in 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus 48.31 at Title Page, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus “de fasciis - Opera Hippocratis et Galeni” 17, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 18 (1).777. (2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista 43 gives ἡ χ.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>] in <i>signification</i> 1, and in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PS” p.125B. gives ὁ χ. in signification 11, compare 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 1.162; but this distinction is not observed by later writers.) \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5482","accentedUnicode":"χάραξ","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5480","matchingForm":"χάραγμα","stepTransliteration":"charagma","gloss":"image/mark","_zh_tw_Gloss":"印記","_es_Gloss":"imagen/marca","_zh_Gloss":"印记"},{"strongNumber":"G5481","matchingForm":"χαρακτήρ","stepTransliteration":"charaktēr","gloss":"reproduction","_zh_tw_Gloss":"真像","_es_Gloss":"reproducción","_zh_Gloss":"真像"}],"shortDef":"barricade, palisade (a defensive line or fence)","mediumDef":"barricade, palisade (a defensive line or fence) <br /><b>a stake; a</b>, military <b>palisade, rampart,</b> formed from the earth thrown out of the ditch, and stuck with sharp stakes or palisades, <ref='Luk.19.43'>Lk. 19:43</ref>*","stepGloss":"barricade","stepTransliteration":"charax","count":1,"_es_Definition":"barricada","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 木樁 (經外含意)<br>2) 柵欄, 壕溝 (路 19:43)","_zh_Definition":"1) 木桩 (经外含意)<br>2) 栅栏, 壕沟 (路 19:43)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"một chiến hào.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"土壘","_es_Gloss":"barricada","_zh_Gloss":"土垒"}]}